<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Check whether the DIE for this MDNode can be shared across CUs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit-2/#ad426154fed29e102c17d745b44cf2006"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit-2/#ad426154fed29e102c17d745b44cf2006">DwarfUnit::isShareableAcrossCUs</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dinode">DINode</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a6a9f043784cf87001c84980afa76da82">D</a>)</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When the MDNode can be part of the type system, the DIE can be shared</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// across CUs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Combining type units and cross-CU DIE sharing is lower value (since</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cross-CU DIE sharing is used in LTO and removes type redundancy at that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// level already) but may be implementable for some value in projects</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// building multiple independent libraries with LTO and then linking those</span></CodeLine>
